            0.46773287,
            0.45627667
        ],
        "ans_top4_original_plus_artifact__small_artifact_60_90": "The clustering algorithm in the paper is based on Gaussian Mixture Models (GMMs). The primary challenge it faces is the high dimensionality of vector embeddings, which can cause distance metrics to behave poorly in high-dimensional spaces (the 'curse of dimensionality'). To mitigate this, the authors use UMAP for dimensionality reduction. Additionally, the Gaussian assumption in GMMs may not perfectly fit the sparse and skewed distribution of text data, though empirical results show it remains effective for their use case. The system\u2019s computational efficiency, demonstrated by linear scaling of build time with document length, supports the viability of GMMs for large-scale text clustering.",
