        "ans_top4_original_plus_artifact__small_artifact_60_90": "The pseudo code for step 5 of the tree traversal method is:\n\n```python\nfor layer in range(tree.num_layers):\n    topk = []\n    for node in S_current:\n        score = dot_product(query, node)\n        topk.append((node, score))\n    S_layer = sorted(topk)[:k].nodes  # Select top-k nodes by cosine similarity\n    S_current = S_layer  # Update current layer to the next layer's top-k nodes\n```\n\nThis loop iteratively processes each layer of the tree, selecting the top-k nodes based on cosine similarity to the query embedding and propagating the search to deeper layers. The recursion is implicit in the repeated iteration over layers, ensuring the algorithm traverses the tree depth-wise to collect context from all levels.",
